  "prompt": "Female Tinder users of Bangalore, the hell do you expect when you write in your profile \"not looking for hook ups\"?",
  "response": "When female Tinder users in Bangalore write \"not looking for hookups\" in their profiles, they are likely trying to set clear expectations about the type of relationship they want. This statement typically conveys that they are interested in more meaningful connections, whether that be friendship, companionship, or a serious relationship, rather than casual encounters.\n\nPeople may interpret this in various ways, and some may be respectful of those intentions, while others might not read it seriously. It's important for users to be aware of the dynamics of the dating app environment and craft their profiles in a way that reflects their desires while filtering out those who might not align with them. Ultimately, setting clear boundaries can help in attracting more compatible matches.",
